reviews.text: É claro que não seria algo grandioso pois o Governador Valadares é uma cidade pequena. Ademais, havia uma área não completa que parecia ser meio abandonada. No entanto, o conteúdo apresentado neste museu é muito informador sobre a cidade, verdadeiramente aprendi muito sobre a cidade do meu pai e senti mais orgulho da história da minha família. Além do mais, a arquitetura antiga preservada agrada os olhos. O atendimento também foi ótimo, as moças que trabalham lá conversavam conosco e nos ofereciam mais informações sobre o museu e a cidade. É uma pena que muitos não conhecem este museu, pois realmente vale a pena o visitar para conhecer cada vez mais a nossa história!
Uma excelente opção para conhecer a história de Governador Valadares. O acervo poderia melhorar. A planta original da cidade precisa de restauração urgente.
Me surpreendeu. Apesar do espaço ser alugado, tem muitos atrativos e retrata a história da cidade. Mais pessoas deveriam conhecer.
Relembrei de coisas que fizeram parte da minha família e da minha vida.

Disappointment.  The menu looked great online and on the window but when my wife and I sat down we were handed a stained paper menu with about 6 salads and 6 entrees.  My choice wasn't on the list and had to try the "leg" of lamb.  It turned out to be a dry, recooked lamb steak with little flavor.  My wife's gnocci was bland except for the excessive use of garlic.  If they spent half the time working on making the food better as they do designing the plate it might be edible.  DO NOT GO!
Excellent Italian food. The bruschetta was the best I have ever had, and the sauce over the sweet potato gnocchi was great. One of my top three restaurants in Cville
One of Kingston's hidden gems! Wok-In has a small storefront but has the best Thai/Cambodian food in town. The owners are so sweet & their portions are big! Very fair pricing but limited seating

Great food, awesome prices, and incredibly fast service. Owners are really friendly. Great spot to pop in for some truly authentic thai food. Some of the best i've ever had. All made fresh to order with huge portions.
Huge portions and great quality for amazing prices. Was full before I was even half done, will definitely be going back! 😊

I've been coming here for 25 years. The food is unmatched. Everything is made from scratch and the portions are huge. The place is tiny and you may have to wait for your food or a table, but it is so worth it. If you enjoy SE Asian food do not miss the Wok Inn.

A Kingston institution for good reason, though I think the phrase "you get what you pay for"really applies here. Very affordable, but don't expect anything fancy, especially for dining in.  We had a #14 (so-so) and a #15 (very good). Generous portions. Counter service, and the food is all cooked to order. The main problem is the meals take up to 50 minutes depending when you go, and don't come at the same time when you dine in.

I cannot recommend this enough. Definitely one of the best meals I've ever had, arguably the best. Absolutely delicious. I had a sharing meat platter thing. Unbelievable. Friendly staff too. Highly recommend!!!
Delicious and original food at reasonable prices. Nice and helpful staff. Pleasant atmosphere. Definitely worth a visit.

Lovely service and delicious food. For me, the fitfit was the highlight, but my friends loved the gorgeous coffee (and frankincense). It was all a delight for the senses. This wasn't my first time there, nor will it be my last.
Really delicious food and good service, very pleasant staff.  Had the vegetarian sharing dish and it was more than enough for two people.
Delicious food, perfectly spiced and authentically Eritrean! A taste explosion for both vegans and meat eaters alike.
